HEADWORD: Wolfish
<hw>Wolf"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a wolf; having
the qualities or form of a wolf; <as>as, a <ex>wolfish</ex> visage;
<ex>wolfish</ex> designs.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wolf"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wolf"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

